                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I somehow negotiated my way into a Tipt group the other day.
<br />

<br />
Picked up a mean, 1274 hitting pet.  For fun, hasted and dual wielded it. Now comes the interesting part.
<br />

<br />
With this pet the aggro transfer was so bad that if I cast any spell at all on the victim mob it would beeline to me.
<br />

<br />
Tash at 10% health - beeline.
<br />

<br />
Slow at any percent - beeline.
<br />

<br />
Any nuke, even the Ceramic band - beeline.
<br />

<br />
I had to dispell haste from my pet to be able to slow the incoming mobs without getting creamed.
<br />

<br />
I think that I understand what was happening.  But am I alone in noticing this?   Why hasn't anyone mentioned it if not?
<br />

<br />
Edit: Yes, there was a BoC equipped warrior in the group, and it didn't matter.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
