                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A portion of the pets agro will transfer to you, as the owner of the pet.
<br />

<br />
In PoP and GoD, if there are enough targets on an npc's agro list, he will ignore all pet agro, but will not ignore you.
<br />
The limit is 4 targets (have not tested all of GoD, but seems consistant):
<br />
You
<br />
Pet
<br />
Tank
<br />
Tank's healer
<br />

<br />
If there are 4 or less targets, then the mob will stay in melee range with the pet, who I'm sure has the highest agro due to dps, but will engage the PC in range with the highest agro.
<br />

<br />
Once there are more than 4 targets, the mob will ignore pet agro completely, and will make a beeline for whoever is *really* at the top of the agro list.
<br />

<br />
This is how pet agro works in PoP, and I believe all of GoD.  The rest of Norrath, including LDON, doesn't have this 4 target pet agro rule, and pets are abit easier to (ab)use.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.botsguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

<br />
