                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I'll assume then, that you have more than 3 people in your group, and that the mob will ignore pet agro.  This doesn't sound like a true bug to me, but rather an inherent limitation of the agro transfer system in its current form.  It was probably not designed to handle that much dps difference.
<br />

<br />
There is a difference between passive agro and active agro.
<br />
Passive is acquired without directly doing anything to the mob.
<br />
i.e. proximity agro, assist agro, and being a pet owner.
<br />

<br />
Active agro is acquired by directly interacting with a mob.
<br />
i.e. damage, debuffs, stun, etc.
<br />

<br />
(note: exception to this is casting dispel on a mob results in passive, not active agro)
<br />

<br />
What you are probably having an issue with, is that the percentage of agro that transfers from your pet is higher than the agro that the warrior is able to maintain.  As your pet is hitting hard and fast, he is staying a step ahead of the warrior every round, even on a successful taunt by your tank.  Rangers noticed this problem a while back, as they went for faster weapons for more dps, and noticed their agro easily overtook a warrior's. 
<br />

<br />
--
<br />

<br />
Did your warrior engage first, or did the pet?
<br />
I find that if my pet establishes enough agro initially, and then the 4 target limit is exceeded, the mob will come straight for me, every time.
<br />

<br />
Some things you can do to work around this limitation:
<br />
lower dps of pet, obviously
<br />
stay under the 4 target limit
<br />
delay engaging pet
<br />
use boggle
<br />
use root
<br />
use stun
<br />
tank</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.botsguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

<br />
